column3:
29/79

Nina always was a workaholic. I had to plan our dates, get Kamil to block her calls while we were out. But she always made time for me.

Now? She's in the lab past midnight, every night, always working on some new strain, making sure we have something ready for next week. And the week after that. And the week after that.

The quotas keep getting worse. They're over 200 a week now. Most of that burden falls on her. It's killing her. It's killing us.
